WRITING.TITLE: I was shamed for being bisexual in front of other classmates back in middle school
WRITING.TEXT: So back in middle school, there was this popular girl who did sports. During class one day she was asking everyone about their sexuality. Our school was pretty open about stuff like this so most people said what their sexuality is. I, said bisexual and everyone is like okay cool y #8217;know. The popular girl gives me a look. She says, #8220;Bisexuals are just lonely horny people looking to f*ck anyone they can and they always cheat. #8221; Those exact words. I remember them exactly even though this was years ago because of everyone else #8217;s reaction. They all either laughed or agreed. I tried to laugh along, but it hurt to be shamed like that. What made me even more upset though? The popular girl was very openly lesbian. I never really thought other LGBTQ+ people would be biphobic until that that day. Anyway I just felt like sharing this experience of bigotry.
